"1348":"1348","1325":"1325","1456":"1456","1302":"1302","1346":"1346","1367":"1367","1411":"1411","1344":"1344","1365":"1365","1364":"1364","1386":"1386","about 1411":"about 1411","Biggar, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Biggar, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Pen-Llin, Ogmore, Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","Penllin, Ogmore, Glamorganshire, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Castell y Mynack, Pentyrch, Glamorgan, Wales":"Pentyrch, Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Penllyn, Glamorgan, Wales":"Penllyn, Glamorgan, Wales","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fleming","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: ethnic name for someone from Flanders, from Middle English <i>fleming</i>. The word reflects a Norman French form of Old French <i>flamanc</i> ‘Fleming’, from the stem <i>flam-</i> + the ancient Germanic suffix <i>-ing</i>. In the Middle Ages there was considerable commercial intercourse between England and the Netherlands, particularly in the wool trade, and many Flemish weavers and dyers settled in England. This surname is also common in south and east Scotland and in Ireland, where it is sometimes found in the Gaelicized form <b>Pléamonn</b>.","German: variant of   Flemming  , cognate with 1 above."],"variants":[{"name":"Flemings","meanings":["English: plural form of   Fleming  .","Americanized form of Flemish <b>Vleminckx</b>: patronymic from <b>Vleminck</b>, an ethnic name for someone from Flanders, Middle Dutch <i>vleminc</i>."]},{"name":"Flanders","meanings":["English: ethnic name from Middle English <i>Fla(u)ndres</i> ‘Flanders’, denoting someone from Flanders, a historical region covering parts of modern-day Belgium, France, and the Netherlands. Compare   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Fleeman","meanings":["English: variant of   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Flemming","meanings":["German: ethnic name for someone from Flanders, Middle High German <i>vlaeminc</i>. People from Flanders spread throughout Germany, as well as England, in the Middle Ages as clothmakers and dyers.","English: variant of   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Flamenco","meanings":["Spanish: ethnic name from <i>flamenco</i> ‘Fleming, Flemish person’ (see   Fleming  )."]}]},{"name":"Jenkin","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, which is derived from the medieval given name <i>Jankin</i>. This was a pet form of the boy's name   Jan  , with the diminutive suffix <i>-kin</i>. The modern given name is popular in Wales, where the surnames <i>Jenkin</i> and <i>Jenkins</i> are common."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Jenkin Fleming was born in 1344, in Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, John Fleming, was 42 and his mother, Efa Norreys, was 20. He married Alice Rayne in 1364, in Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1456, in Wales, United Kingdom, at the age of 112."},"et":{"1344–1456":"1344–1456","1346–1374":"1346–1374","1348–Female":"1348–Surnud","1365–Female":"1365–Surnud","1390–Male":"1390–Surnud","1365–1411":"1365–1411","1302–1386":"1302–1386","1325–1367":"1325–1367","about 1390":"umbes 1390","1374":"1374","1390":"1390","1348":"1348","1325":"1325","1456":"1456","1302":"1302","1346":"1346","1367":"1367","1411":"1411","1344":"1344","1365":"1365","1364":"1364","1386":"1386","about 1411":"umbes 1411","Biggar, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Biggar, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Pen-Llin, Ogmore, Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","Penllin, Ogmore, Glamorganshire, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Castell y Mynack, Pentyrch, Glamorgan, Wales":"Pentyrch, Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Penllyn, Glamorgan, Wales":"Penllyn, Glamorgan, Wales"},"fi":{"1344–1456":"1344–1456","1